com.unvired.ump.agent

Interface ISAPRFCRequest

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IUMPRequest, java.io.Serializable

    public interface ISAPRFCRequest
extends IUMPRequest
    The interface ISAPRFCRequest provides an abstraction to make JCo calls to a SAP ABAP WebAS. 
      Sample code for a JCo call to BAPI_TRANSACTION_COMMIT. The code assume that the required proxy classes 
  are generated using the Unvired designer.  
   
  public void execute(IBusinessProcess process)
  {
      //Create an instance of the generated proxy class
      BAPI_TRANSACTION_COMMIT bapi_transaction_commit_rfc = new BAPI_TRANSACTION_COMMIT();
  
      //Set the input parameters
      bapi_transaction_commit_rfc.setWAIT("X");
  
      //Execute the request
      ISAPRFCRequest rfcRequest = (ISAPRFCRequest)process.createObject(RequestType.RFC);
      rfcRequest.setFunction(bapi_transaction_commit_rfc);
  
      //Process the response
      ISAPRFCResponse rfcResponse = (ISAPRFCResponse)process.getService().submitRequest(bapi_transaction_commit_rfc,"");
      RETURN returnValue = bapi_transaction_commit_rfc.getRETURN();
  }
